3EYou%20have%20to%20keep%20breaking%20your%20heart%2C%20until%20it%20opens.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%88%BC%20Rumi%20(1207%E2%80%931273)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20heart%20was%20made%20to%20be%20broken.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%88%BC%20Oscar%20Wilde%20(1854%E2%80%931900)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBlessed%20are%20the%20hearts%20that%20can%20bend%3B%20they%20shall%20never%20be%20broken.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%88%BC%20Albert%20Camus%20(1913%E2%80%931960)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHearts%20will%20never%20be%20practical%20until%20they%20can%20be%20made%20unbreakable.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%88%BC%20Tin%20Man%20in%20The%20Wizard%20of%20Oz%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhat%20is%20stronger%20than%20the%20human%20heart%20which%20shatters%20over%20and%20over%2C%20and%20still%20lives%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%88%BC%20Rupi%20Kaur%20(b.%201992)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20quotes%2C%20dating%20back%20three%20thousand%20years%2C%20demonstrate%20the%20repeated%20use%20throughout%20human%20history%20of%20the%20metaphoric%20broken%20heart%20in%20literature%2C%20philosophy%2C%20and%20religion.%20Even%20today%20the%20concept%20of%20breaking%20one%E2%80%99s%20heart%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20most%20known%20and%20used%20metaphors.%20But%20can%20strong%20emotions%20truly%20break%20a%20heart%3F%20Well%2C%20yes%2C%20they%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20tiger%20chases%20you%2C%20a%20number%20of%20changes%20will%20happen%20in%20your%20body%3B%20this%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20fight%20or%20flight%20response.%20The%20amygdala%20in%20your%20brain%20triggers%20a%20signal%20telling%20your%20body%20to%20run.%20That%20signal%20travels%20to%20the%20adrenal%20glands%2C%20where%20the%20adrenal%20medullae%20release%20adrenaline.%20The%20adrenaline%20quickly%20makes%20its%20way%20to%20your%20heart%E2%80%99s%20pacemaker%20cells%20and%20speeds%20up%20your%20heart%20rate.%20It%20also%20causes%20heart%20muscle%20cells%20to%20let%20in%20more%20calcium%2C%20which%20makes%20them%20contract%20harder.%20This%20provides%20oxygenated%20blood%20to%20your%20leg%20muscles%20so%20you%20can%20run.%20However%2C%20on%20occasion%2C%20the%20body%E2%80%99s%20stress%20system%20can%20run%20amok%20and%20damage%20the%20heart%2C%20causing%20a%20stress-induced%20heart%20attack.%3Cbr%3E%5CnStress-related%20heart%20attacks%20are%20also%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9Cbroken%20heart%E2%80%9D%20or%20takotsubo%20syndrome.%20Takotsubo%20is%20Japanese%20for%20%E2%80%9Coctopus%20pot.%E2%80%9D%20First%20described%20in%201990%2C%20Japanese%20physicians%20were%20observing%20patients%2C%20mostly%20women%2C%20who%20suffered%20a%20heart%20attack%20after%20experiencing%20acute%20severe%20emotional%20grief%20or%20stress.%20Their%20heart%20dysfunction%20made%20their%20left%20ventricle%20look%20like%20an%20octopus%20pot%E2%80%94a%20pot%20with%20a%20wide%20bottom%20and%20a%20narrow%20neck.%20These%20patients%20had%20classic%20signs%20and%20symptoms%20of%20a%20heart%20attack%3A%20chest%20pain%2C%20elevated%20heart%20enzymes%2C%20EKG%20changes%2C%20and%20regional%20heart%20wall%20motion%20abnormalities.%20But%20on%20cardiac%20catheterization%20their%20coronary%20arteries%20were%20found%20to%20be%20free%20of%20atherosclerotic%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20307px)%2085vw%2C%20307px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31160958%2F9789356404540.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22307%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31160958%2F9789356404540.jpg%20400w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31160958%2F9789356404540-188x300.jpg%20188w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691108%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22491%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EVincent%20M.%20Figueredo%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Curious%20History%20of%20the%20Heart%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EBloomsbury%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20majority%20of%20broken%20heart%20syndrome%20cases%2C%20heart%20function%20recovers.%20We%20know%20that%20the%20resulting%20abnormal%20shape%20of%20the%20Takotsubo%20heart%20reflects%20the%20distribution%20of%20adrena-%20line%20receptors%20in%20the%20normal%20heart%20muscle%2C%20but%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20exactly%20why%20stress-induced%20heart%20attacks%20happen.%20A%20sudden%20surge%20of%20adrenaline%20can%20damage%20heart%20cells.%20Studies%20after%20earthquakes%E2%80%941994%20in%20Northridge%2C%20California%2C%20and%201995%20in%20Kobe%2C%20Japan%E2%80%94found%20that%20the%20incidence%20of%20heart%20attacks%20was%20much%20higher%20on%20the%20day%20of%20the%20earthquake%20than%20on%20the%20same%20day%20the%20previous%20year.%20In%20addition%2C%20during%20and%20immediately%20after%20World%20Cup%20penalty%20shoot%20outs%20and%20Super%20Bowls%2C%20a%20surge%20in%20stress-induced%20heart%20attacks%20occurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESudden%20severe%20emotions%2C%20or%20acute%20stress%2C%20can%20cause%20a%20heart%20to%20literally%20break.%20Fortunately%2C%20in%20many%20cases%20that%20broken%20heart%20recovers%20and%20the%20patient%20survives.%20As%20the%20seventeenth-century%20English%20poet%20Lord%20Byron%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20heart%20will%20break%2C%20but%20broken%20live%20on.%E2%80%9D%20Under%20no%20other%20conditions%20do%20the%20metaphorical%20heart%20and%20the%20biological%20heart%20intersect%20more%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20we%20surprised%20that%20lifelong%20couples%20tend%20to%20die%20within%20months%20of%20each%20other%3F%20Johnny%20Cash%20and%20June%20Carter%20Cash%20died%20within%20four%20months%20of%20each%20other.%20The%20theory%20is%20that%20death%20of%20the%20surviving%20spouse%20follows%20quickly%20during%20bereavement%20because%20of%20the%20intense%20physical%20stress%20of%20grief%E2%80%94and%20a%20broken%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20single%20saddest%20moment%20of%20my%20career%20occurred%20when%20I%20was%20a%20cardiology%20fellow.%20Stepping%20out%20of%20a%20patient%E2%80%99s%20room%2C%20I%20had%20to%20inform%20her%20husband%20of%20over%20sixty%20years%20that%20his%20wife%20had%20passed%20away.%20He%20knew%2C%20as%20well%20as%20we%20did%2C%20that%20she%20was%20not%20going%20to%20survive.%20But%20as%20I%20told%20him%20the%20news%2C%20I%20watched%20his%20face%20melt%20into%20such%20anguish%20and%20fear.%20He%20looked%20up%20at%20me%20and%20asked%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20do%20I%20do%20without%20her%3F%E2%80%9D%20The%20sorrow%20in%20his%20eyes%20hurts%20me%20to%20this%20day.%20He%20grabbed%20my%20shoulders%20for%20support%20and%20kept%20looking%20at%20me%20for%20an%20answer.%20I%20held%20this%20small%20man%20in%20my%20arms%20and%20cried%20with%20him%20for%20a%20long%20time%20that%20day.%20He%20passed%20away%20five%20months%20later%20in%20hospice%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20all%20of%20our%20science%20and%20the%20disillusionment%20of%20the%20heart%20as%20nothing%20more%20than%20a%20pump%2C%20these%20cases%20seem%20to%20describe%20moments%20when%20the%20emotional%20and%20physiological%20parts%20of%20our%20heart%20become%20one.%20The%20sixteenth-century%20anatomist%20Gabriele%20Falloppio%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CMan%20cannot%20live%20with%20a%20broken%20heart.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20emotions%20we%20feel%20in%20our%20brain%20reverberate%20in%20our%20heart%2C%20and%20the%20resulting%20physical%20sensations%20are%20manifestations%20of%20the%20heart%E2%80%99s%20response.%20This%20interdependence%2C%20the%20heart-brain%20connection%2C%20is%20vital%20to%20our%20health.%20It%E2%80%99s%20what%20led%20humans%20over%20thousands%20of%20years%20to%20place%20our%20emotions%2C%20reasoning%2C%20and%20very%20soul%20in%20this%20hot%2C%20pumping%20organ%20that%20signifies%20we%E2%80%99re%20alive.%20Ancient%20societies%20taught%20that%20a%20happy%20heart%20meant%20a%20happy%20body%20and%20a%20long%2C%20healthy%20life.%20Modern%20science%20and%20medicine%20are%20now%20suggesting%20that%20our%20ancestors%20may%20have%20been%20more%20insightful%20than%20once%20thought.%20It%20may%20be%20that%20the%20heart%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20our%20emotional%20and%20physical%20well-being%20is%20more%20significant%20than%20what%20physicians%20and%20scientist%20have%20led%20us%20to%20believe%20in%20the%20past%20five%20hundred%20years.%20It%20may%20be%20that%20the%20heart%20talks%20to%20the%20brain%20as%20much%20as%20the%20brain%20directs%20the%20heart%2C%20and%20that%20this%20heart-brain%20connection%20plays%20a%20vital%20role%20in%20our%20overall%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20with%20permission%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Curious%20History%20of%20the%20Heart%3Cem%3E%20by%20Vincent%20M.%20Figueredo%2C%20published%20by%20Bloomsbury.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVincent%20M.%20Figueredohas%20been%20a%20practicing%20cardiologist%20and%20physician-scientist%20for%20thirty%20years.%20His%20experience%20spans%20academic%20medicine%2C%20medical%20research%2C%20teaching%2C%20private%20practice%2C%20and%20senior%20hospital%20administration%2C%20including%20as%20chair%20of%20cardiology%20and%20professor%20of%20medicine.%20Figueredo%E2%80%99s%20research%20interests%20include%20how%20the%20heart%20responds%20to%20injury%2C%20alcohol%2C%20and%20stress.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704019520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31161331%2Frobina-weermeijer-qIK_fc-4fmw-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fstrong-emotions-could-literally-break-your-heart%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sudden%20severe%20emotions%2C%20or%20acute%20stress%2C%20can%20cause%20a%20heart%20to%20literally%20break.%20Fortunately%2C%20in%20many%20cases%20that%20broken%20heart%20recovers%20and%20the%20patient%20survives.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fs