s%20in%20Southern%20California.%20The%20money%20was%20good%20enough%20that%20he%20didn't%20need%20any%20other%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20years%20later%2C%20Juan%20is%20still%20a%20full-time%20gig%20delivery%20worker.%20But%20he's%20running%20out%20of%20options%20to%20stay%20that%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20Juan%20said%2C%20he%20gets%20fewer%20offers%20through%20the%20apps.%20Those%20that%20do%20pop%20up%20on%20his%20screen%20are%20gone%20in%20a%20second%20or%20two%20if%20he's%20not%20quick%2C%20a%20change%20he%20attributes%20to%20more%20people%20in%20his%20area%20getting%20into%20delivery%20work.%20He's%20also%20tried%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20other%20apps%2C%20including%20Amazon%20Flex%2C%20Grubhub%2C%20and%20DoorDash%2C%20but%20hasn't%20gotten%20off%20waitlists%20for%20them.%20%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20they're%20not%20taking%20more%20drivers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B2020%20and%202021%20were%20excellent%2C%20but%20things%20started%20to%20go%20downhill%20in%202022%20and%20now%202023%2C%26quot%3B%20Juan%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpokespeople%20for%20Amazon%2C%20DoorDash%2C%20and%20Grubhub%20confirmed%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20they%20put%20prospective%20delivery%20workers%20on%20waitlists%20in%20certain%20markets%20based%20on%20demand%20for%20deliveries.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20several%20months%2C%20I've%20spoken%20with%20roughly%20three%20dozen%20people%20who%20work%20for%20Instacart%2C%20DoorDash%2C%20Walmart's%20Spark%2C%20and%20other%20delivery%20services%20that%20rely%20on%20gig%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20those%20conversations%20included%20a%20common%20theme%3A%20Working%20as%20a%20delivery%20driver%20got%20a%20lot%20harder%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20Lots%20of%20workers%20tell%20me%20that%20they%20got%20into%20delivering%20early%20in%20the%20pandemic%20when%20lots%20of%20people%20were%20willing%20to%20pay%20extra%20to%20have%20groceries%2C%20takeout%2C%20and%20other%20things%20brought%20to%20their%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%20things%20are%20harder.%20Just%20finding%20orders%20to%20deliver%20can%20be%20a%20challenge.%20Some%20services%2C%20like%20Instacart%2C%20have%20also%20cut%20base%20pay%20for%20delivering%20orders.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-make-money-gig-worker-uber-lyft-doordash-delivery-driver-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELess%20than%2010%25%20of%20gig%20workers%20make%20over%20%242%2C000%20a%20month%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20according%20to%20research%20from%20PayQuicker%2C%20a%20payments%20company%20with%20clients%20in%20the%20gig-work%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20of%20the%20problems%20that%20delivery%20gig%20workers%20faced%20in%202023%2C%20varying%20from%20lower%20pay%20to%20greater%20competition%20to%20sudden%20deactivations.%20Several%20workers%20declined%20to%20have%20their%20names%20used%2C%20citing%20potential%20retaliation%20from%20the%20apps.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20their%20identities%20and%20status%20as%20gig%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20competition%2C%20lower%20pay%2C%20and%20a%20rigid%20schedule%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20delivery%20services%20have%20pitched%20themselves%20for%20years%20to%20workers%20who%20don't%20want%20a%20rigid%209-to-5%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202015%20worker%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finstacart.wordpress.com%2F2015%2F08%2F17%2Finstacart-shoppers-profile-greg%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etestimonial%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Instacart%20is%20a%20great%20example.%20Titled%20%26quot%3BHow%20Instacart%20shoppers%20are%20achieving%20big%20dreams%20on%20a%20flexible%20schedule%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20features%20%26quot%3BGreg%20F.%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20aspiring%20actor%20who%20made%20ends%20meet%20delivering%20orders%20for%20Instacart.%20%26quot%3BMy%20availability%20changes%20every%20week%20in%20terms%20of%20rehearsals%20and%20auditions%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20quote%20from%20Greg%20in%20the%20testimonial%20reads.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20can%20accommodate%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20working%20for%20the%20apps%20has%20started%20to%20look%20more%20like%20an%20office%20job%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20working%20at%20a%20specific%20time%2C%20workers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-shoppers-wait-in-parking-lots-to-claim-orders-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EInstacart%20encourages%20shoppers%20to%20hang%20out%20in%20parking%20lots%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20near%20busy%20areas%20identified%20using%20color-coded%20heatmaps%2C%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20earlier%20this%20year.%20The%20company%20says%20that%20being%20near%20a%20busy%20store%20improves%20shoppers'%20chances%20of%20stanching%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20contrast%20with%20past%20years%20when%20many%20shoppers%20could%20claim%20an%20order%20from%20home%2C%20even%20if%20they%20were%20miles%20away%20from%20a%20store.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20you're%20not%20really%20free%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20shopper%20in%20Utah%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20locked%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20Instacart%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20its%20contractors%20spend%20less%20than%2010%20hours%20each%20week%20doing%20work%20for%20the%20app.%20%26quot%3BOverwhelmingly%2C%20shoppers%20say%20they%20choose%20to%20earn%20income%20through%20the%20Instacart%20platform%20because%20of%20the%20freedom%20and%20independence%20they%20get%20with%20a%20flexible%20schedule%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Instacart%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20driver%20for%20DoorDash%20in%20California%20said%20he%20doesn't%20mind%20waiting%20in%20parking%20lots.%20But%20he%20says%20doing%20other%20things%20on%20his%20phone%20to%20pass%20the%20time%2C%20like%20watching%20YouTube%20videos%2C%20has%20made%20him%20miss%20out%20on%20decent%20orders.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20being%20clocked%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20be%20on%20your%20phone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContractors%20for%20Walmart's%20Spark%20delivery%20service%20also%20have%20to%20show%20up%20in%20store%20parking%20lots%20once%20an%20hour%20in%20order%20to%20claim%20orders.%20Once%20they%20pull%20into%20a%20spot%2C%20they%20open%20the%20Spark%20app%20by%20the%20appointed%20time%2C%20which%20varies%20by%20store%2C%20and%20then%20claim%20an%20order%20or%20batch%20of%20orders%20they%20want%20to%20deliver.%20A%20Walmart%20associate%20is%20then%20supposed%20to%20whisk%20the%20order%20out%20of%20the%20store%20and%20into%20their%20car.%20In%20practice%2C%20though%2C%20stores%20are%20so%20overwhelmed%20that%20they%20face%20delays%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-spark-drivers-over-hour-waiting-orders-in-parking-lots-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eof%20an%20hour%20or%20more%20filling%20Spark%20orders%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20in%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20Spark%20orders%20are%20filled%20on%20this%20hourly%20drop%20schedule%2C%20one%20worker%20in%20Texas%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20can%20literally%20pull%20up%20at%2C%20let's%20say%2C%2012%3A39%2C%20and%20I%20am%20one%20minute%20too%20late%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20driver%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20get%20anything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Walmart%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider%20in%20October%20that%20orders%20make%20it%20out%20to%20drivers%20in%2010%20minutes%20or%20less.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20focused%20on%20giving%20drivers%20an%20efficient%20pick-up%20experience%20and%20maximizing%20their%20earning%20opportunities%2C%20so%20we%20consider%20the%20time%20it%20takes%20to%20dispense%20orders%20when%20determining%20earnings%20for%20each%20trip%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20there's%20competing%20with%20all%20the%20other%20gig%20workers.%20Instacart's%20gig%20workforce%20has%20swelled%20to%20600%2C000%2C%20and%20Walmart%20estimates%20that%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20of%20thousands%26quot%3B%20of%20people%20have%20made%20deliveries%20for%20Spark.%20Yet%20demand%20for%20the%20delivery%20of%20many%20items%2C%20especially%20groceries%2C%20has%20tapered%20off%20since%20the%20early%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20translates%20to%20lower%20earnings%20for%20many%20workers.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20cannot%20live%20off%20of%20%2430%2C%20so%20they%20have%20to%20find%20something%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Spark%20driver%20in%20Texas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDelivery%20app%20workers%20have%20realized%20that%20pay%20isn't%20reliable%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20lots%20of%20gig%20workers%2C%20delivering%20groceries%2C%20takeout%2C%20and%20other%20stuff%20just%20isn't%20paying%20the%20bills%20like%20it%20used%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexia%20Hudson%20spent%20two%20years%20delivering%20orders%20for%20Instacart%20in%20the%20area%20around%20Charlotte%2C%20North%20Carolina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%20July%2C%20two%20months%20before%20its%20IPO%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-cuts-minimum-base-pay-for-drivers-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EInstacart%20cut%20its%20minimum%20payment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20group%20of%20orders%20from%20%247%20to%20%244.%20Hudson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20pay%20cut%20meant%20the%20job%20didn't%20make%20sense%20for%20her%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20she%20has%20started%20a%20full-time%20job%20and%20has%20stopped%20delivering%20for%20Instacart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20these%20updates%2C%20we%20expect%20average%20pay%20to%20stay%20the%20same%20for%20shoppers%20across%20the%20platform%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20Danker%2C%20chief%20product%20officer%20at%20Instacart%2C%20said%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20pay%20cut.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20not%20all%20orders%20are%20created%20equal%2C%20and%20we%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20shopper%20earnings%20reflect%20the%20effort%20needed%20to%20fulfill%20each%20batch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20have%20followed%20Hudson%20in%20throwing%20in%20the%20towel%20on%20gig%20work.%20Demand%20for%20delivery%20services%20has%20fallen%20since%20early%20in%20the%20pandemic%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-economy-boom-over-labor-market-jobs-bank-of-america-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereport%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Bank%20of%20America%20Institute%20published%20in%20April%20found.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20wages%20for%20most%20full-time%20jobs%20have%20risen%2C%20leading%20many%20who%20relied%20on%20gig%20work%20for%20their%20income%20to%20apply%20for%209-to-5%20work%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20old-fashioned%20job%20might%20also%20come%20with%20more%20security%20than%20working%20for%20gig%20apps.%20Some%20independent%20contractors%20have%20learned%20the%20hard%20way%20that%20you%20can%20be%20booted%20from%20an%20app%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-shopper-won-280000-in-arbitration-after-deactivation-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehonest%20mistake%20at%20the%20Walmart%20self-checkout.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20gig%20workers%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20October%20that%20once%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-gig-workers-are-fighting-against-sudden-account-deactivations-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edeactivated%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20have%20little%2C%20if%20any%2C%20opportunity%20to%20appeal%20the%20decision%20and%20get%20reinstated.%20The%20companies%2C%20including%20Instacart%2C%20Grubhub%2C%20DoorDash%2C%20and%20Uber%2C%20said%20that%20they%20have%20appeals%20processes%20and%20that%20drivers%20who%20haven't%20done%20anything%20wrong%20can%20be%20reactivated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20laws%20in%20some%20big%20cities%20aim%20to%20improve%20conditions%20for%20gig%20workers.%20In%20Seattle%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20laws%20mandating%20that%20some%20gig%20workers%20get%20sick%20days%20and%20a%20minimum%20hourly%20wage%20of%20%2417.27%20will%20take%20effect%20in%20January.%20Another%20city%20ordinance%2C%20which%20requires%20gig%20apps%20to%20provide%2014%20days%20of%20notice%20to%20workers%20they%20intend%20to%20deactivate%2C%20takes%20effect%20in%202025%2C%20GeekWire%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.geekwire.com%2F2023%2Fseattle-approves-first-of-its-kind-law-that-protects-app-based-workers-from-deactivation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20a%20state%20appeals%20court%20judge%20upheld%20a%20New%20York%20City%20law%20that%20would%20require%20DoorDash%2C%20Grubhub%2C%20and%20Uber%20to%20pay%20food%20delivery%20workers%20at%20least%20%2417.96%20an%20hour%20%E2%80%93%20the%20city's%20minimum%20wage%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2023%2F12%2F01%2Fbusiness%2Fuber-doordash-and-grubhub-must-pay-ny-workers-18-per-hour%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20New%20York%20Post.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20that%20employ%20delivery%20workers%20oppose%20the%20laws.%20Target-owned%20delivery%20service%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftargets-shipt-to-suspend-delivery-in-seattle-report-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EShipt%20has%20even%20said%20that%20it%20will%20suspend%20operations%20in%20Seattle%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20next%20month%2C%20days%20before%20that%20city's%20new%20laws%20take%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20workers%2C%20like%20Juan%20in%20Southern%20California%2C%20getting%20out%20of%20the%20gig%20economy%20entirely%20seems%20like%20a%20better%20option.%20%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20the%20slice%20of%20the%20pie%20is%20getting%20smaller%20and%20smaller%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20looking%20for%20a%20proper%20job%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20Instacart%2C%20Walmart%20Spark%2C%20or%20another%20gig%20delivery%20service%20and%20have%20a%20story%20idea%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20abitter%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgolden-age-gig-work-instacart-doordash-delivery-jobs-over-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704017221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658f35ed1c5c7b8c9a0d0607%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgolden-age-gig-work-instacart-doordash-delivery-jobs-over-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Workers%20for%20Instacart%2C%20DoorDash%2C%20Grubhub%2C%20Walmart%20Spark%20and%20other%20apps%20say%20delivery%20gigs%20got%20harder%20in%202023%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgolden-age-gig-work-instacart-doordash-delivery-jobs-over-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20car%20launches%20in%202024%3A%20New%20Kia%20Sonet%20to%20Hyundai%20Creta%20facelift%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704016992000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106419272%2Cimgsize-1290735.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fauto%2Fcars%2Fnew-car-launches-in-january-2024-new-kia-sonet-to-hyundai-creta-facelift%2Farticleshow%2F106419214.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20Sonet%20will%20be%20offered%20in%20three%20engines%20an