ms.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year%20that%20we%20leave%20behind%20was%20a%20sombre%2C%20troubled%20one%20both%20for%20India%20and%20for%20much%20of%20the%20world.%20The%20politics%20of%20hate%20engulfed%20more%20and%20more%20people.%20Bombs%20pitilessly%20pounded%20children%20and%20hospitals%20in%20Gaza%20on%20a%20scale%20not%20seen%20this%20century%2C%20civilians%20picked%20up%20firearms%20against%20each%20other%20converting%20Manipur%20into%20an%20implacable%20war%20zone%2C%20and%20lynchings%20continued%20in%20India%2C%20barely%20noticed%20any%20more.%20Democracy%20faltered%2C%20inequality%20further%20soared%20and%20India%20fell%20even%20further%20in%20the%20Global%20Hunger%20Index%20rankings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20fitting%2C%20then%2C%20that%20the%20marker%20of%20the%20worthiest%20of%20Hindi%20films%20and%20shows%20of%202023%20was%20a%20common%20strain%20of%20dogged%20humanism%20%E2%80%93%20of%20idealism%2C%20courage%20and%20hope%20%E2%80%93%20even%20as%20they%20acknowledged%20the%20crises%20of%20inequality%2C%20injustice%20and%20hate%20that%20cobble%20the%20lives%20of%20ordinary%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20instructive%20that%20six%20of%20the%20nine%20films%20and%20shows%20listed%20here%20are%20based%20on%20true-life%20stories.%20And%20even%20those%20that%20are%20fictional%20are%20close%20to%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20front%20line%20among%20my%20favourite%20films%20was%20one%20that%20came%20early%20in%20the%20year%2C%20Nandita%20Das%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EZwigato%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20narrative%20of%20aching%20tenderness%20and%20gentle%20rage.%20Das%20carefully%20observes%20the%20quiet%20struggles%2C%20the%20dignity%2C%20the%20resolve%2C%20the%20hurt%20and%20the%20determined%20love%20of%20Manas%20Mahto%2C%20a%20middle-aged%20food%20delivery%20man%2C%20and%20Pratima%20who%20steps%20out%20warily%20to%20share%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20burdens%2C%20as%20a%20masseuse%20to%20rich%20women%20in%20high-rise%20apartments%20and%20as%20a%20janitor%20in%20a%20mall.%20With%20luminous%20empathy%2C%20Kapil%20Sharma%20and%20Shahana%20Goswami%20portray%20how%20both%20try%20to%20hide%20from%20the%20other%20from%20the%20humiliations%2C%20the%20insults%20and%20disappointments%20that%20they%20endure%20as%20they%20daily%20grapple%20with%20the%20uncaring%2C%20unequal%20world%20of%20rich%20and%20middle-class%20India.%20Their%20unostentatious%20but%20steadfast%20love%20for%20each%20other%20and%20for%20those%20in%20their%20care%20forms%20the%20moral%20core%20of%20the%20film%2C%20and%20in%20the%20end%20its%20only%20fount%20of%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31114728%2Fdownload-18.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31114728%2Fdownload-18.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31114728%2Fdownload-18-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31114728%2Fdownload-18-1024x576.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691078%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKapil%20Sharma%20and%20Nandita%20Das%20on%20the%20sets%20of%20%E2%80%98Zwigato%E2%80%99.%20Photo%3A%20IMDB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20this%20same%20stubborn%20humanism%20that%20drew%20me%20to%20the%20mini-series%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Railway%20Men%3A%20The%20Untold%20Story%20of%20Bhopal%201984%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecompellingly%20directed%20by%20Shiv%20Rawail.%20It%20chooses%20to%20tell%20the%20story%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20worst%20industrial%20disaster%20that%20took%2015%2C000%20lives%20and%20ravaged%20several%20hundred%20thousand%20others%20by%20centre-staging%20narratives%2